  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. These typically involve financial institutions and other businesses having to:\n\n1. Conduct customer due diligence\n2. Report suspicious transactions to relevant authorities\n3. Maintain transaction records\n4. Train staff to recognize potential money laundering activities\n\nSpecific requirements vary by jurisdiction, but most developed countries have robust anti-money laundering (AML) regulations.",
